main event: A weather balloon was observed for more than one hour over Lake Andes, South Dakota on January 30, 1956.
interesting points: The object was observed by a civilian while watching the construction of a water tower.
The object was observed for more than one hour and did not display any discernible flight path or maneuvers.
The reporting officer concluded that the sighting was generated by a weather balloon, probably of the radiosonde type.
The weather conditions at the time of the sighting were clear and cold, with calm winds.
The Air Defense Command was notified about the sighting.
